<br>
The staff I was using before was 6.9 damage, 3.2 delay, 80% quality (store bought).<br>
<br>
The staff I got from the quest was 7.5 damage, 5.0 delay, 100% quality, 5% bonus.<br>
<br>
I looked at them, and thought to myself that the one I already had must be better. 6.9/3.2 versus 7.5/5.0? no contest, surely, even with a better quality rating, and a 5% bonus.<br>
<br>
I decided to double check, and equipped the new staff and went into the Tomb of Mithra to test it.<br>
<br>
Holy shiznit! This new staff was so much better than the old one, it wasnt even funny. Blue con mobs were dying in 3 hits, yellow cons in 4. I was hitting for 70-80 damage per hit, and I did one crit for exactly 150 damage.<br>
<br>
It didnt make sense. I went from hitting mobs for 40ish damage with a 6.9 damage weapon, to hitting for 80ish damage with a 7.5 damage weapon.<br>
<br>
Basically, this post is a warning to old EQ players who are set into the 'dam/delay' mindset from EQ. When looking at a weapon, damage and delay only play one part of many when determining the weapon's value. Quality, material, bonus.. all seem to play a large part.<br>
<br>
And before anyone asks, both staffs were yellow con to me.<br>
<br>
Zadkiel. <p><TABLE BORDER=0 ALIGN=CENTER>
